Title: ITT 12/2017 - International communications market data collection
Description:
Ofcom publishes its annual ICMR in the first week of December each year. The 2016 report is available here:
https://www.ofcom.org.uk/research-and-data/cmr/cmr16/international

The requirement is for delivery of a survey of data from a variety of sources, across all communications sectors, including quantitative consumer research from a range of countries including European countries, the USA and Australia, as research for and for reference in Ofcom's International Communications Market Report (ICMR). Output should be supplied in two forms, one in an Excel-based format according to the Ofcom designed template, and the second in an Excel spreadsheet according to the successful tenderers design.

As a minimum, the service must deliver the following:
• Provide datasets as detailed within the ITT for the countries listed, for the 2017 and 2018 (and 2019 if Ofcom choose to extended the Contract to 3 years) ICMR reports. Backdated data to 2011 must also be provided.
• Provide a source for all the datasets provided.
• Supply all data by 1 September each year for 2017, 2018 according to the 2 year agreement (and 2019 if Ofcom choose to extended the Contract to 3 years).
• Supply all data in spreadsheets using the same Ofcom provided template each year for each country.
• Clear all data for use in our publications.
• Support Ofcom as it analyses the data and prepares its report over the period
September to November in 2017 and 2018, as well as 2019 if the contract is extended to the full 3 year term.

Title: Prosperity Fund Framework
Description:
Foreign and Commonwealth Office invited tenders from suitably experienced contractors to join the new £1.3 billion, Cross-Whitehall Prosperity Fund framework. The Fund's primary objective is to promote inclusive economic growth and poverty reduction, in accordance with Official Development Assistance
rules and the International Development Act.

There were two overall focuses Lot A: Enabling Environment and Lot B: Specialist Sectors.
Lot A consists of diverse skills organised into one 'Enabling Environment' Lot for business which incorporates Business Environment (incl. Anti-Corruption), Finance and Trade.   (A1 Business Environment, A2 Finance Trade, A3 Trade, A4 Managed Service). 

Lot B consist of more specialist sector requirement (B1 Infrastructure, Lot B2 Future Cities, B3 Energy, B4 Digital, B5 Health, B6 Education and B7 Managed Services)

The framework will commence on 1 April 2018 and continue for a period of 2 years initially with (1 + 1  year extensions).
